    <string name="full_description"><![CDATA["
Usually calendar entries are shared in the human-unreadable technical format "ICS" (or "VCS") that calendar
programs can read.

CalEF receives the technical format and re-sends/re-shares it-s content as human readable text.

## Requirements:

* Android-4.4 (api 19).
* Permissions : None

## Compatible with

* [Etar-Calendar](https://f-droid.org/en/packages/ws.xsoh.etar) version 1.0.29 or later (January 2022)
* [Simple-Calendar](https://f-droid.org/packages/com.simplemobiletools.calendar.pro) version 4.0.0 or later (May 2018)
* Buildin Android-Calender (Tested with android-10 on LG device)


"]]></string>
